<item>
            <title>[SOLR-719] Persisting solr.xml through SolrJ does not handle relative pathes correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-719</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems the code in CoreContainer.persistFile should begin with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  /** Persists the cores config file in a user provided file. */
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void persistFile(File file) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (file != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !file.isAbsolute())
        file = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File(configFile.getParentFile(), file.getPath());
    log.info(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Persisting cores config to &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + (file==&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; ? configFile : file));
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue today resides in calling file.getName() instead of file.getPath()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
